canonical:
  title: 禮部侍郞林光讓監試試官不允
  author: 無名氏
  language: lzh
  text: 朕循祖宗間歲之制受郡國賓賢之書大闢成均坌集多士思得英翹之輩以爲異日梁棟之材姸媸之形宜覈其實考校之柄故難其人爾學術恢通鑒識精敏足堪是任以副所期云何牢辭欲替成命無以易爾往其懋哉
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 禮部侍郞林光讓監試試官不允
  author: 無名氏
  language: lzh
  text: 朕循祖宗間歲之制。受郡國賓賢之書。大闢成均。坌集多士。思得英翹之輩。以爲異日梁棟之材。姸媸之形。宜覈其實。考校之柄。故難其人。爾學術恢通。鑒識精敏。足堪是任。以副所期。云何牢辭。欲替成命。無以易爾。往其懋哉。
korean:
  title: 예부시랑 임광 양 감시시관 불윤
  author: 무명씨
  language: kor
  text: 짐이 해를 걸러 한 번씩 인재를 뽑는 조종조의 제도에 의거하여 각 지방에서 올린 현재(賢才)를 추천하는 문서를 받아, 성균관(成均館)을 활짝 열어놓고 많은 선비들을 한곳에 모은 다음 그중에서 영특한 인물을 뽑아 후일 국가의 동량(棟梁)이 될 재목으로 삼으려 한다. 그런데 잘나고 못난 것은 마땅히 그 실지를 살펴보아야 하는바, 고시(考試)의 책임을 맡을 적임자를 얻기가 힘들다.그대는 학술에 넓게 통달하여 감식안이 정밀하고 민첩하니, 이 중임을 맡아 기대를 충족할 만하다. 그런데 어찌 굳이 사양하여 내린 명을 바꾸려고 하는가. 바꿀 수 없으니 직(職)에 나아가 힘쓸지어다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0330_010_0200&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: The King's Edict to Minister Lin Guang, Declining His Refusal of the Supervisory Examination Post
  author: Anonymous
  language: eng
  text: Following the ancestral precedent of selecting talent once every other year, I have received the recommendations of worthy men from the provinces. The gates of the National Academy stand wide open, gathering scholars from all quarters. Among them I seek those of exceptional brilliance, to become the pillars and beams of our nation's future. Yet how to discern the true from the false? The burden of examination falls upon a man of uncommon gifts. Your learning spans wide, your judgment keen and swift. You are the one fitted for this heavy charge, to fulfill the hopes I have placed. Why then do you insist on declining? Why seek to alter my command? There is no one to replace you. Go forth to your post and do your utmost.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'ancestral precedent of selecting talent once every other year' refers to the triennial civil examination system, a cornerstone of East Asian governance.
  - key: ''
    value: The 'pillars and beams' (梁棟) is a metaphor for able ministers and capable leaders who bear the weight of state responsibility.
  - key: ''
    value: This piece represents the king's formal response to a minister's repeated refusal of appointment, emphasizing imperial authority and confidence in the minister's abilities.
